  "prompt": "What exactly is the vijay mallya case?",
  "response": "The Vijay Mallya case is a high-profile legal and financial scandal involving Indian businessman Vijay Mallya. Here's a detailed overview of the case:\n\n### Background\nVijay Mallya is a well-known Indian businessman who was the chairman of United Breweries Group and the owner of the now-defunct Kingfisher Airlines. He was once considered a prominent figure in Indian business and social circles.\n\n### The Case\nThe case primarily revolves around allegations of fraud and loan default related to Kingfisher Airlines. Here are the key aspects:\n\n1. **Loan Default**:\n   - Kingfisher Airlines, owned by Mallya, accumulated significant debt, primarily from loans taken from a consortium of Indian banks led by the State Bank of India (SBI).\n   - The total debt was reported to be around \u20b99,000 crore (approximately $1.3 billion).\n   - Mallya and Kingfisher Airlines failed to repay these loans, leading to accusations of default.\n\n2. **Allegations of Fraud**:\n   - It was alleged that Mallya diverted funds from the airline for his personal use and other businesses, rather than using them to keep the airline afloat.\n   - These actions were seen as fraudulent and a violation of the trust placed in him by the lending banks.\n\n3. **Legal Actions**:\n   - In 2016, Mallya left India for the United Kingdom and has been fighting extradition ever since.\n   - The Indian government, through the Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) and the Enforcement Directorate (ED), has pursued legal action against him.\n   - Mallya was declared a \"wilful defaulter\" by Indian banks, and several cases were filed against him in Indian courts.\n\n4. **Extradition Proceedings**:\n   - In 2017, India formally requested Mallya's extradition from the UK.\n   - After a prolonged legal battle, in 2019, a UK court ruled in favor of extraditing Mallya to India.\n   - However, Mallya appealed this decision, and the case has been ongoing in the UK courts.\n\n5. **Asset Seizure**:\n   - Indian authorities have attempted to recover some of the owed money by seizing Mallya's assets in India.\n   - Properties and other assets linked to Mallya have been attached or auctioned off to recover the dues.\n\n### Current Status\nAs of my last update, Vijay Mallya's extradition case was still pending in UK courts. He continues to face multiple legal battles in India related to the fraud and default allegations.\n\n### Impact\nThe Vijay Mallya case has had a significant impact on the Indian banking sector and has led to increased scrutiny and regulatory measures aimed at preventing similar incidents in the future. It has also sparked debates about corporate governance, accountability, and the legal framework surrounding financial fraud in India.\n\nThis case remains a landmark in Indian financial and legal history, highlighting issues of corporate fraud and the complexities involved in international extradition and asset recovery.",
